In the face of "epidemic disease" , one's strength may be limited

But the strength of a crowd is enough to survive the winter

On February 16, Zhang arrived in Wuhan with a fleet of vacuum ambulances. Earlier, affected by the epidemic, Highway Service area suspended food and beverage services, he and his driver brothers can only live on instant noodles, dry food.

"I'm definitely going, and there's nothing you can do to stop me. " Before he volunteered for Midea's convoy, his family objected vehemently to his going to the affected area. But chun-tien knew that the negative pressure ambulances were a lifesaver.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Unlike ordinary ambulances, the most important feature of a negative-pressure ambulance is that it can prevent pollution from the outside world and the environment inside the vehicle, and minimize the risk of cross-infection among medical and nursing personnel inside and outside the vehicle, the utility model is mainly used for the safe isolation and transportation of the patients with major infectious diseases.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 24th, 13 cities in Hubei closed down their cities, leaving a huge gap in medical supplies across the province. In the epidemic in the critical stage of the ramp, the entire community's emergency reserves ushered in the big test. A group of "retrograde" is through their own forces, trying to drill wood fire, with the warmth of light to illuminate the land.

15 days accelerated production, 2000 km love relay

On January 26, the group of anti-"epidemic" materials procurement team received a special task, procurement of 140 negative-pressure ambulances donated to the Hubei Epidemic area.

This is not for the beauty of the car business, the difficulty is self-evident. On the same day, a group including the United States high-level, finance, legal, taxation, including the "epidemic commando" quickly formed.

Made hundreds of calls in 36 hours, eventually locking down 12 automakers on the morning of January 28th. However, due to the need for customized production of negative-pressure ambulances, vehicle manufacturers generally delivery time in March.

"The earlier the minute arrives, the earlier the minute saves the life" , the United States' team launches the communication with the Automobile Enterprise Veronica Guerin, finally under the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology and other government departments' strong support, the first batch delivery time clinches on February 10.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the evening of January 29th, the first orders were signed. Although it was the Chinese New Year holiday, it took only 24 hours to negotiate demand from January 28 to rush payments and confirm orders.

Orders are confirmed, but a new round of snags seems to have just begun. During the outbreak, the factory faced two major problems: shortage of core components such as negative pressure equipment and shortage of workers. Faced with the "near-impossible task, " a coordinated relay race ensued.

Midea immediately asked the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology for support, designated suppliers to provide the necessary chassis and other accessories for assembling the negative pressure ambulance, and deployment of negative pressure isolation system, negative pressure isolation chamber and other equipment, working together to help the parties to solve synchronously, compress production time.

At the Brilliance Renault plant in Shenyang, workers who had voluntarily given up their vacation braved the freezing cold of minus 15 degrees Celsius by shunting and transporting cars in outdoor parking lots to get them to the plant for renovation as quickly as possible. As a result, the 30-day renovation period was reduced to less than 15 days.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After hard work, the 5th batch of 40 negative-pressure ambulances produced in Shenyang was completed, but they had to travel 2,000 kilometers to Hubei, which undoubtedly posed a great challenge to the scheduled 16-day delivery. Zhang was one of 13 drivers, all of them volunteers, who took over the baton from Liaoning long haul.

"The road was very slippery and trucks could not change lanes at will. Traffic police were in front to clear other vehicles, " Zhang recalled.

At that time, a large-scale snowstorm hit the north and south of China, the transport team is passing through Tianjin, Snow caused high-speed closure, inch-by-inch difficult to move. Miit immediately contacted the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology and local transportation departments, including the Hubei Department of Communications, for assistance. An hour later, Tianjin Highway Traffic Police Brigade arrived and escorted the convoy to Hebei.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Subsequently, Hebei, Henan, Hubei Traffic police continue to relay, until the convoy safely arrived in Wuhan. Traffic police in Tianjin and Henan also prepared hot meals for drivers, which touched Zhang, who had to eat instant noodles on the way.

"because we are drivers, sending supplies here is the same as normal work, but we go to different places, " Zhang said, embarrassed by the traffic police's salute. "listening to him, I feel like I have done a good deed. "

At present, the last batch of 18 sets of negative pressure ambulance from Wuxi, has arrived at Wuhan Dahualing Railway Station at about 4:00 am on February 20. At this point, the United States procurement donations of 140 negative-pressure ambulances have been put in place, into the war "epidemic" front.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Hubei Province, another relay race is still going on.

Through the cold winter night, a foot throttle to continue to move forward

"I am not tired, they are the most dangerous, the most tired people ah, the fight against the epidemic depends on them, I just do something within my power. " Sang Fu looked at sitting in the hospital corridor dozing doctors and nurses, very distressed. He had just delivered supplies to Ezhou's Mount Thor Hospital.

On the night of January 26th, in Suizhou, about 400 km from Wuhan, Sangshi received a phone call asking if he would be willing to participate in the distribution of relief supplies. He did not hesitate.

At that time, it was the third day of the city closure. Midea Group, which has a complete warehousing and logistics system in Wuhan, donated large quantities of materials to the fire God mountain, Thunder God mountain and Hubei County and city hospitals. And assume the task of relief supplies point-to-point delivery is the United States under the umbrella of the United Nations Logistics Company, Master Sang is one of the drivers.

On January 27, Master Sang, who had traveled from Suizhou to Wuhan, showed up at the company's warehouse on time. He had no idea that the job he knew so well was facing many challenges.

At 7:00 in the morning, master sang began his work, delivering a shipment of supplies to the Thor Mountain Hospital in Ezhou. But the road to Ezhou has become so muddy because of the continuous rain that the trucks are at constant risk of getting bogged down. Once trapped, they need to deploy on-site excavators to help push the cart, Sangshi always make hands and feet are mud.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Every day after the last one, usually late at night. Considering that he often in and out of the hospital, Sangshi did not dare to go home, for fear of causing cross-infection to the people around him, he prepared a quilt in the car, every night in the car to rest, one opened his eyes, then continue to work.

Sensei Sang, who endured each cold winter night, often missed his family, who worried him day and night, but he chose to drive in Wuhan after the siege because there were more people he wanted to protect.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
There are many more drivers like sang in Andezhilian. They will run through more than 70 designated hospitals in Hubei Province and hand-deliver relief supplies to doctors.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The "retrograde one" is on his way

No one can stay out of the current outbreak. Chi-aid Wuhan, chi-aid Hubei, in the wake of the sense of social responsibility of Chinese enterprises, but also let enterprises collectively face a responsibility test.

Some say it is the second big test since the 2008 earthquake in Wenchuan County. What is different is that after 12 years, Chinese enterprises have risen to a new stage in fulfilling their responsibilities, and the whole society has become more rational in its evaluation of public welfare. It was realized that the amount of donations was not the only thing that mattered, and that what was defined as the best aid was how companies could use their superior resources and expertise to maximize the effectiveness of relief efforts based on the needs of the affected areas.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
It is worth mentioning that this epidemic in the Spring Festival special node, coupled with the city, home isolation and other measures to increase the difficulty of assistance to enterprises, but enterprises with strong allocation of resources will have the ability to move quickly. Globalization has long been defined as the main route to the future of the United States, and today, 43 percent of the group's operating income comes from overseas markets, where it has accumulated resources over the years, for the front-line materials, "fill the gap" to provide a strong basis.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Facing the shortage of front-line materials in Hubei, Midea is taking advantage of global products, channels, resources and teams, and using "Midea speed" to send the most useful help to the front line in time: starting from January 24, the first batch of products were delivered to the construction site of the Huoshenshan hospital on the 26th, and 100 million RMB were donated to the Hubei Epidemic Area for the global purchase of anti-epidemic materials, within a week, the global "Haitao" to 3 million medical masks, nearly 40,000 pairs of disposable medical gloves, the first batch of 525,000 South Korean medical masks arrived in Wuhan on January 31..

As for any enterprise, the course of social responsibility will be adjusted with the change of its own position and external cognition of its role. For the United States in revenue of more than 260 billion yuan, continuous adjustment and innovation of products and business, is a normal enterprise development, this idea is also integrated into the public good. Just as Midea proved that they are professional, efficient and innovative in carrying out their social responsibilities by donating a negative-pressure ambulance, which is "not a good thing" .

It comes from Midea's many years of experience in doing her duty. Like many great companies that incorporate social responsibility into their corporate strategies, Midea has been exploring ways to build sustainable social responsibility systems. Over the past 20 years, Mei's founders, he Xiangjian and Mei's group, have invested more than 7 billion yuan in poverty alleviation, disaster relief, old age care, education and other charity areas. They have initiated and implemented various social responsibility projects, not only to help those in need, also exercise their own "combat" ability.

Beauty of the deep understanding, in the face of the "epidemic" , a person's strength may be limited, but a group of people's strength, but enough to survive the winter. In the rescue, the United States has joined forces with the government, relevant car companies, the logistics system and many other parties. The Split Second has ensured that every link will not be broken, which not only reflects the responsibility of Chinese private enterprises, also has fully demonstrated the development to grow up the Chinese private enterprise's power of action and the appeal.

The ever-changing external environment puts pressure on all businesses to break their habits. For more than 50 years, leadership, resilience, and quick action have been key to America's constant search for change. In this war "epidemic" , the United States uphold this concept, as a "retrograde" one of the rush in the front.

Along the way, and with more people along the way, we are one step closer to the goal we aspire to.
